This documentation provides an overview of how to plan a Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) installation.

##<a id='overview'></a>Overview

In planning a PCF installation, you should:

- Review the Requirements for your IaaS.

- Refer to the Reference Architecture for your IaaS.

- Assess your platform needs, including capacity, availability, container support, host OS, resource isolation, and geographical distribution. Discuss with your Pivotal contact.

For all of the above, the specifics depend on the IaaS that you are deploying PCF to. So the contents of this documentation are organized by IaaS.

